name: r-stars
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.5-5" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-stars
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/stars_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/stars/stars_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: f359577c9e08066cb9ea6aab9b8eae574efea95ba6efcc250663f2c350fe8b41

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-abind
    - r-classint >=0.4_1
    - r-lwgeom
    - r-rlang
    - r-sf >=0.9_7
    - r-units
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-abind
    - r-classint >=0.4_1
    - r-lwgeom
    - r-rlang
    - r-sf >=0.9_7
    - r-units

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('stars')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('stars')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://r-spatial.github.io/stars/, https://github.com/r-spatial/stars/
  license: Apache-2.0
  summary: Reading, manipulating, writing and plotting spatiotemporal arrays (raster and vector data cubes) in 'R', using 'GDAL' bindings provided by 'sf', and 'NetCDF' bindings by 'ncmeta' and 'RNetCDF'.
  license_family: APACHE
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - xhochy
